revision.text:
In [[applied mathematics]], a '''doubly linked face list''' ('''DLFL''') is an efficient [[data structure]] for storing [[Topological manifold|2-manifold]] mesh data. The structure stores [[linked list]]s for a 3D mesh's faces, edges, vertices, and corners. The structure guarantees the preservation of the [[manifold]] property.<ref>{{citation | last = Chen | first = Jianer | doi = 10.1016/S0304-3975(96)00273-3 | issue = 2 | journal = [[Theoretical Computer Science (journal)|Theoretical Computer Science]] | mr = 1465274 | pages = 247–266 | title = Algorithmic graph embeddings | volume = 181 | year = 1997}}.</ref><ref>{{citation | last1 = dos Santos | first1 = Thiago R. | last2 = Meinzer | first2 = Hans-Peter | last3 = Maier-Hein | first3 = Lena | doi = 10.1142/S0218195911003767 | issue = 4 | journal = International Journal of Computational Geometry & Applications | mr = 2826033 | pages = 467–494 | title = Extending the doubly linked face list for the representation of 2-pseudomanifolds and 2-manifolds with boundaries | volume = 21 | year = 2011}}.</ref>
